<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">*notice: this is a combo rant/question.<P>I just dinged 35 this morning and sat to med for the first time.  What a pleasant experience it is to see what is happening instead of just reading about it.  I feel like I just went from Radio to TV...it seems that this level may just be the point where things really change for me as a "Drunken Dwarven Battlecleric".  I see that my spells are getting stronger, but so are my foes.<P>What are your thoughts regarding the path to level 39?  Right now, I'm raiding 1-2 times per week, grouping in guild another 1-2 times, and hunting solo or pickups another 1-2 nights per week.  I have done this to get the experience of all the different styles of play, both outdoors and underground.<P>Now for the rant, how many of you brother Clerics get upset by Warriors telling you not to meele, even though you are at FM?  I hate this, as I have an offensive skill at 173, defensive skill at 152 and dodge at 169, along with 1HB maxed out for level already (175).  Heck, I even have my swimming over 160!<P>I have spent a lot of effort maintaining my meele skills, I am after all, a Battlecleric.  What's the point of Plate Mail if you sit in the dew-covered grass, letting it gather rust?  I have had to explain to the tanks many times that it does our group no good if I sit there at full mana, waiting to heal them, but not doing anything else.  I can do 25-33 damage with my Dark Ember (even though it doesn't proc for me yet), or 18-22 with the smoldering brand (which does proc Burn for 14dd about every 8-10 swings).  I switch back and forth, using the SB when I want to do many blows (i.e. following a runner) and + strength, or the DE for + stats and a steady-heavy damage without building too much aggro.  These guys (MT/MA) also seem to forget that I can self buff to 1,250+ hp, so I can take alot of meele damage (for this level of MOB).  <P>I know, we are healers, but why must we be forced into becoming a bunch of one-trick ponies when we really are a pretty well rounded class.<P>Piikaa Fishweed<BR>35th Drunken Dwarven Battlecleric of Brell<BR>Bertoxxulous Server<BR>Proud member of Twilight Order<p>[This message has been edited by piikaa (edited 02-05-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Feias</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In the slim chance that it isn't a typo but a lack of knowledge on my part I have to ask for clarification.<P>Doesn't Dodge cap out at 75?<P>Also can you actually self buff to 1250+ at 35?  If you can Are you very well equipped or just decently.  I want to know if I am did something wrong. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Typo, Dodge @ 69...<P>Piikaa</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With the gear I have on, plus Guard, Valor and Symbol, my hp showed 1257 this morning.<P>I have several +hp items on, so that does help too.<P>Piikaa</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DurokH</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Battle on, Battle Cleric!  At least while you can, and let the people you group with know this.  You may want to team up with some other clerics and take on undead - that would be great!  And I suppose as long as people stay buffed/healed, who cares?<P>At some point, though, you will become useless in melee and will find yourself doing the heal/buff/crowd control duties.  I'm, not much of a tank, but once in a while I like to mix it up.  My skills aren't bad, and I wield a Dark Ember (decent enough 1HB), but for the last couple levels I barely dent a mob (You hit for 1!).<P>So, enjoy it while you can....<P>Durok<BR>52nd Cleric</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Javara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I like to get up and swing a weapon once in a while also, however as I have seen it pointed out various times in other threads it is probably more efficient to throw a nuke or to stun the mob and then med that mana back than it is to melee for the same amount of time. Many times when you join pick up groups people are there for the exp as quick and efficiently as they can get it, so in those instances I try and be as efficient myself.<P>However when grouped with friends and guildies they know I am a "good" cleric and don't mind if I use my pathetic meelee skill some, given it isnt endangering the goup of course, as we are there to have fun mostly and get loot/exp second. Course in my case I don't have a dark ember either <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P> <P>------------------<BR>Javara Mendor<BR>Brell Serilis Server<BR>48th Level</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corish-MT</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm (checks stats screen)....<P>Including Armor of Protection I'm up to 1378 self-buffed at level 35.  Cheap spell (only a few plat) that you pickup (or have someone fetch) in Iceclad at the Gnome Pirate outpost.<P>I'm a high-elf with maybe 50 points of +HP gear.  But with Symbol (300pts), Valor (200pts), and Armor of Protection (200pts) is what gets me to almost double my base stats of around 780 or so.<P>------------------<BR>Corish, 35 Cleric of Morell-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Balamor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Whenever i can keep my mana maintained and dont feel like nuking, i whip out my 2-hander and start hitting the mobs. No one has ever had a problem with this, considering I only do it when i have mana coming outta my ears. In fact, i even started meleeing Fayl Everstrong in POG when we were farming POG armor on a weekly basis like 3 months ago :P<P>------------------<BR>Balamor<BR>60 Dwarf High Priest<BR>Soldiers of Light<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">jhonno torv</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If your mana is at 80 percent or greater, its none of the tanks business what you are doing, as long as you aren't screwing him up.<P>You can use whatever heals you like, you can hit stuff, you can cast nukes.  The only time he should offer advice is if you are consistently running low on mana, and he knows of a way to save some.<P>Ask him this, "Do I tell you how to hit stuff?  Do I tell you when to taunt?  No, you do your job well, and I respect that.  I do my job well too, can't you respect me?"<P>The only exceptions to this would be if you were gaining aggro, and not able to cast a heal spell when needed.<P>My general response to meat shields that offer advice is: "Thank you."<P>I then think about it, and if I think their idea has a chance to speed the flow of exp or loot, then I try it a couple times.<P>I can say this.  You are approaching the point where the amount of melee damage you can do is being outweighted by the amount of spell damage you can do.  You will be better off medding the extra time, then getting off a nuke or a stun.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know the nukes do more damage, but the meele is still better for not gaining aggro.  I also don't want my meele skills to atrophy, since I realize I won't be using them much later in my career (at least not on MOB's that I can raise my skills with).  I like being able to use my meele too in a pinch, when I don't have time to med and the MOB is almost dead in a critical situation.<P>Piikaa Fishweed<BR>35th Drunken Dwarven Battlecleric of Brell<BR>Bertoxxulous Server<BR>Twilight Order</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">daku inochi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Play the way you like.  If someone objects, then tell them to stick their opinion back IN their ass and when you need it, you'll ask them for it.  Until then, STFD and STFU.<P>While you are no longer a viable damage-dealing class in melee, you CAN do a few different things at 35:<P>Heal and sit and emote funny stuff (You'll have time)<BR>Heal/Stun to mitigate damage<BR>Heal/Melee (if you have a proc'ing weapon)<BR>Heal/Nuke to help kill it faster still<P>No matter what happens, play the game the way *you* like to play it. As long as no one dies and you've all had fun, you've done your job.<P>Here's how I respond to those "Heal Me!" pleas:<P>Warrior (low on health):  Heal!!!<BR>Daku: Slash!!!<BR>Warrior (lower on health): Heal now!!<BR>Daku: <sigh>  Dude.. you play YOUR character, let me play mine.  Trust me - you're not going to die.<BR>Warrior: Heal!  Heal!  Heal!!<P>/em resists the temptation to let this idiot succumb to his wounds.<P>/em casts Complete Heal and heals the Warrior to full.<P>Daku: Okay, MY job is done.. now.. how come this critter ain't dead yet??? <grin><P>Don't let ANYONE tell you how to play the game.<P>Daku<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ykryoon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/agree Jhonno and Daku<P>Heck, if you have plenty of mana and are confident you can deal with whatever comes along, forget smacking the one that everybody else is beating up... grab a spirit of the 