Arial">Hehe, yes the cleric nuking (or even meleeing) is often a signal to the tank to pull more ;p.<P>Velma's group was hunting in Kaesora this week in front of the library.  Even keeping everyone fully buffed (though I let symbol lapse on all but Scrapy and Daphyne) I was sitting at full mana often enough that I started dotting the current mob and bopping them with my mace, and the enchanter started nuking for the kill too.  <P>Just about the point I decided to keep the warrior at 2 bubbles whenever possible (cause everything was blue & he likes being beserk) he brought back a crowd.  Scrapy lived and so did everyone else, but we were rather low mana at the end of the fight.  But he'd figured we were pulling too slow because Daphyne and I were nuking.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Velma Dinkley<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darianne</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>The Darianne Foundation for young battle clerics supports a clerics wish to do whatever they want as long as it doesn't endanger the group  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I melee.  I nuke.   I pull (just added Howling Stones to my list of places).   I heal.   Have fun.<P>Telling people how to play thier character is messy business.   First of all... everyone can have different views on whats "right" or "best".   I think bards are a perfect example... some groups get a bard and just say "Sit and play mana song".   Other bards play a wide variety of songs.<BR>Sometimes people don't do things... I've had druids not snare... tanks who I think don't taunt... enchanters who don't stun casters.   Just gotta see what works, and talk about it nicely.<P>Tanks who tell me to heal tho.. firken pisses me off  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  Whats taunt refresh, 5s?  I think I'll make a hotkey that uses /g WARRIOR_NAME TAUNT NOW! and then pauses for 5s.   Maybe they'll get the clue after awhile  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Want to make a bard friend for life? When they join your group as say "do you want my songs or my sword?" tell them "Honestly-it's totally up to you. You know your class better than I ever could-do what you need to do. If I need mana or something desperately, I'll mention it."<P>I have a couple bards who still throw a tell just to say "hi" every so often that I said that to. This really applies in the 20s and 30s more than anything-by the mid-40s+, most people understand its best to stand back and let the bard do their thing, and only ask for specifics if you need something right away. Of course, if you get in a group that doesn't, feel free to jump in on the bard's behalf. Bard telling someone to back off doesn't carry near the weight of the bard + the cleric.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 53rd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tarf02</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You need to melee because you should get your defense capped.  It is far easier to get raised up at level 40 then it is at level 55.  Mix it up, stand next to rooted mobs, make sure the tanks know you need to get hit, and get your defense raised up.  It is free AC and you always get to have it even when you are dead.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>Tarf</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
